Final 2023 Project: Reflect & Share  

  • Weight: 0
  • Project will start May 24, 2024 6:00 AM, must end by May 31, 2024 6:00 AM

Join Our End of Year Reflection and Celebration! #FacesOfALXSE #ALX_SE

As the year draws to a close, were adding an exciting twist to our curriculum with our Final 2023 Project: Reflect & Share. This is a unique opportunity to conduct a comprehensive audit of your technical growth and your personal evolution, Especially as we ring in the new year.

Working as a Software Engineer requires taking a step back to look and reflect on the tasks youve completed and the products youve built. Now, Think of yourself as both the Engineer and the Product of this years journey. What have you learned, overcome, and achieved in 2023, both in your journey to becoming a software engineer and in life? We invite each one of you to participate in this reflective exercise.

Tasks

0. Reflect on Your Year

mandatory

Take a moment to reflect on your biggest win or lesson of 2023; it could be in the ALX software engineering program or something related. It could be a personal or professional achievement, a growth moment, or a valuable lesson learned.

Please share here a Google doc of your reflection - it must be at least 100 words.

Add URLs here:

1. Document & Share Your Reflection

mandatory

As a software engineer in training, youre embarking on an exercise that mirrors what awaits in your professional future. When you land your first job or advance in your software engineering career, reflective exercises like this will be crucial in assessing your growth and impact. And remember, in this project, you are both the engineer and the product. Facesofalxse will serve as your Manager/Team Lead in this exercise, guiding you through this critical process of self-evaluation and learning.

Read all of the instructions before you get started.

Reflect:

As you compile your milestones/experiences of 2023, consider how youve evolved not just in your technical skills but also as the product of your learning and efforts. What have you developed and refined in yourself this year?
